            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="35464208">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">如果欧埃诺斯真有这技能，并且会循循善诱，那我祝福她。[20c]如果我懂这些，我就会美滋滋的，自我膨胀。

吴飞引 Burnet 註:

[B本注] 苏格拉底的这种自我膨胀，和“循循善诱”的态度正好相反。

ἐμμελῶς: ‘modestly,’ i.e. for so modest a fee (Burnet); at a reasonable price (LSJ, s.v. ἐμμελής); 非吴飞所译「循循善诱」.

ἐκαλλυνόμην τε καὶ ἡβρυνό..</span>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2015-06-26 21:38</span>
                  
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                <blockquote><q>如果欧埃诺斯真有这技能，并且会循循善诱，那我祝福她。[20c]如果我懂这些，我就会美滋滋的，自我膨胀。</q></blockquote><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>吴飞引 Burnet 註:<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div><blockquote><q>[B本注] 苏格拉底的这种自我膨胀，和“循循善诱”的态度正好相反。</q></blockquote><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>ἐμμελῶς: ‘modestly,’ i.e. for so modest a fee (Burnet); at a reasonable price (LSJ, s.v. ἐμμελής); 非吴飞所译「循循善诱」.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>ἐκαλλυνόμην τε καὶ ἡβρυνόμην: These words are opposed to ἐμμελῶς. Socrates means that he would assume a fastidious and disdainful air (and certainly not charge so modest a fee as five minae) for imparting the goodness of a man and a citizen (Burnet); ἐκαλλυνόμην ‘pride oneself in a thing’ (LSJ s.v.); ἡβρυνόμην ‘live delicately; hence, wax wanton, give oneself airs’ (LSJ s.v.).<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>吴飞引 Burnet 而未能得之.
